structuralCueParser.userPromptTemplate:
Question: {{question}}

Return JSON: { "displayColumns": [{ "name": "...", "order": <1-based>, "source": "<short free-text tag describing how this column appeared — bracket, symbol, word, etc.>" }], "groupingHints": ["..."], "hasExplicitColumnRequest": true|false }

If the user did not name any columns at all, displayColumns is empty and hasExplicitColumnRequest is false. Otherwise list every column in the order it appeared, regardless of how it was separated from its neighbours.

schemaLinker.userPromptTemplate:
Question: {{question}}

Schema slice (candidate tables with columns):
{{schemaSlice}}

Identify:
1. requiredTables: minimal table names needed (subset of the candidates).
2. requiredColumns: per-table columns the question references. Each entry: { "table": "...", "column": "...", "reason": "why this column is needed" }.
3. joinHints: how tables connect, if more than one table is required. Each entry: { "from": "TableA", "to": "TableB", "via": "FK or junction-table description" }.

Return JSON EXACTLY this shape: { "requiredTables": [...], "requiredColumns": [...], "joinHints": [...] }
